. It is a human practice aimed at testing and transforming the limits of shared reality, urgently needed in situations where such reality breaks down or turns precarious. Drawing on pragmatist thought, philosophical aesthetics, and art history, Klinger’s account of Richter’s practice offers a highly distinctive conceptual alternative for contemporary art in general.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aArtxPhilosophy. 7aART / General.2bisacsh  aform, theory of art, contemporary art, philosophical aesthetics, pragmatism, painting, Gerhard Richter.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts 2022z9783110992809oZDB-23-DPK08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2022 Englishz978311099281608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2021z97831107391900 cprintz978022634701140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226347295423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226347295/original  a978-3-11-073919-0  University of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-099281-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2022  aZDB-23-DPKb2022